8:
Based on what I've heard, I believe I
know why the academy rejected
you, Couette.
10:
They were probably fearful of you
interfering with the fundamental
basis of their school of magic.
13:
The fundamental basis... of their
magic?
18:
Take the diviners' arts for instance.
This chart illustrates the
fundamental principles of our
magic.
21:
Earth creates metal, metal creates
water, water creates wood, wood
creates fire, and fire creates earth.
This is the cycle that generates.
24:
On the other hand, earth
overpowers water, water
overpowers fire, fire overpowers
metal, metal overpowers wood, and
wood overpowers earth. This is the
cycle that destroys.
33:
This is different from the six
elements that the academy's books
wrote about.
36: But I think it's just as nice.
41:
The problem is, mixing magic from a
variety of fundamental bases is
dangerous. Mix too many, and your
body will reject it. Your very self
could be dismantled.
44:
...That's okay. I've already done that
before.
46:
Even if I forget all the things that
made me happy and sad...
49: I'll just choose to try again.
57:
I shall teach you the core principles
of divining.
68: Okay, is anyone else as lost as I am?
77:
Pretty sure Stella is feeling the same
way right now. Hold tight. I'll whip up
some omurice real quick.
82:
It's so late. Why haven't you eaten
yet?
86:
You said before that you liked eating
dinner with others.
89:
I do too, so I waited. Let's eat
together.
94: Stella. Alk. Can I ask you something?
97:
I'm an only child, and I've always
wanted friends.
99:
Is it okay for me to call you my
friends?
114:
Hehehe... Thanks. This makes me
super happy.
120:
We've got, like, a total sitch on our
tails!
123:
Ahh! Found you, Cou-Cou! This is
literally just the worst! Your parents,
they...
127:
They were taken hostage! Just
totally got SNATCHED by pirates!
139:
Y-yeah, like... Literally no way you'd
make it there todayor even
tomorrow!
144:
If they've taken Couette's parents as
hostages, they definitely don't want
to hurt them until they get what they
want. We shouldn't panic.
149:
Can't the World Flipper send us
flying to them directly?
153:
We're only launched like that when I
don't have exact coordinates...
156:
I can't control where we land when
that happens.
163: There's a chance it can work!
175:
You mustn't be so careless when
you're walking the path of the void.
180: Ah... Ahh... What was I... I'm...
185:
But it seems you won't need my help
this time.
194:
You have steadfast companions by
your side now.
198:
Our next meeting shall be
elsewhere, my dear Couette. Until
then, use your power wiselythis
power that we both share...
204:
Mom! Dad!
Get away from them!
208:
C-come now, Caroline... Surely that's
enough scolding
210:
EXCUSE ME? Is it not a parent's job to
thoroughly scold their child when
said child has misbehaved?
211:
Because YOU won't reprimand our
reckless daughter, that role falls to
ME!
212:
To be fair, the recklessness does
come from your side of the family.
219:
I am grateful beyond words for your
aid in saving us...
220:
As well as how you have watched
over our daughter and facilitated
her growth.
223:
Oh, please. You know she's always
been one to take charge of her own
fate. But she does get a little lonely
from time to time...
227:
You should come visit us in Starview
Village when you have the chance.
230:
That is a wonderful idea. I'll pitch the
idea to Caroline... once her anger
has subsided.
234:
*mumble* I want to chat with
everyone too...
